[Choi Soo Young]

2
00:00:17,750 --> 00:00:19,760
[Gong Myung]

3
00:00:23,830 --> 00:00:26,940
[Kim Sung Ryung]

4
00:00:26,940 --> 00:00:29,150
[Kim Sang Ho]

5
00:00:31,020 --> 00:00:33,500
[Jo Yoon Hee]

6
00:00:46,810 --> 00:00:50,110
[Second Shot at Love]

7
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:02,140
<i>Were you waiting for Geum Ju to call?</i>

8
00:01:02,140 --> 00:01:03,920
<i>I'm just curious.</i>

9
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:05,010
<i>You said she jetted off.</i>

10
00:01:05,010 --> 00:01:07,750
<i>I'm worried if it's something bad
happened like you said.</i>

11
00:01:07,750 --> 00:01:09,560
<i>I'm going to go inside once I sober up.</i>

12
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:10,590
[Did you enjoy the cake we delivered?]
<i>Party?</i>

13
00:01:10,590 --> 00:01:13,250
<i>You went all the way to Seoul
since you can't drink in Bochun?</i>

14
00:01:13,250 --> 00:01:15,360
<i>That's not it.</i>

15
00:01:16,030 --> 00:01:17,920
<i>He was so worried about you.</i>

16
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:19,290
<i>Come on. Let's go.</i>

17
00:01:19,290 --> 00:01:21,100
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

18
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:22,930
<i>I had an inevitable situation.</i>

19
00:01:22,930 --> 00:01:24,400
<i>Whatever that was,</i>

20
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,840
<i>it sounds like it was
a great chance for you to drink.</i>

21
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:29,920
<i>- Let's go.
- Quit drinking.</i>

22
00:01:31,620 --> 00:01:35,270
Aigoo, why is she being like that?

23
00:01:35,270 --> 00:01:38,570
Even though she loved to drink,
it wasn't that bad.

24
00:01:39,670 --> 00:01:41,360
Can't you do something?

25
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:43,230
You're the expert.

26
00:02:08,250 --> 00:02:10,450
<i>Seo Ui Jun killed someone.</i>

27
00:02:10,450 --> 00:02:14,000
<i>He killed someone.</i>

28
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:47,350
[Episode 3: There's a Reason I'm Drunk]

29
00:02:59,890 --> 00:03:01,510
Hi.

30
00:03:01,510 --> 00:03:03,740
You're so early.

31
00:03:03,740 --> 00:03:05,850
Is your stomach okay?

32
00:03:05,850 --> 00:03:07,370
What do you mean?

33
00:03:07,370 --> 00:03:10,370
I heard you went to Seoul to get drunk yesterday.

34
00:03:10,370 --> 00:03:12,930
Seon Uk was pretty upset about it.

35
00:03:13,810 --> 00:03:16,930
Tell him I sincerely apologize.

36
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:19,870
Make sure you apologize to Ui Jun directly.

37
00:03:20,510 --> 00:03:23,850
I thought you two made up,
visiting patients together.

38
00:03:26,490 --> 00:03:29,590
I guess he and I are not meant to make up.

39
00:03:41,070 --> 00:03:42,520
Here?

40
00:03:43,210 --> 00:03:45,470
I don't think there's a serious issue.

41
00:03:45,470 --> 00:03:48,780
- Does it hurt a lot?
- Yeah, I can't turn my head at all.

42
00:03:48,780 --> 00:03:51,300
Oh, I see.

43
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:54,900
- Oh? Someone dropped 50,000 won.
- Where?

44
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:00,370
Geez...

45
00:04:00,370 --> 00:04:01,640
You said it hurts.

46
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,460
But look at you turn your head.

47
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:05,970
What is it? Why did you come?

48
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:08,690
Geum Ju...

49
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:11,360
feels so guilty about yesterday
that she was having trouble eating.

50
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,210
Why don't you stop being mad?

51
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:16,290
I'm not mad. I have no reason to be mad at her.

52
00:04:16,290 --> 00:04:18,750
I'm just bummed about you two.

53
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:21,250
You used to be besties.

54
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:23,300
I won't do it.

55
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:25,740
I won't treat a fake patient, so leave.

56
00:04:25,740 --> 00:04:28,340
Geum Ju is the same as always.

57
00:04:29,030 --> 00:04:31,000
Looking after you.

58
00:04:31,930 --> 00:04:33,980
Why did you take the whole engine out?

59
00:04:33,980 --> 00:04:35,640
That has nothing to do with the accident.

60
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:37,510
His short block engine was old.

61
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:39,460
I figured I'd swap it out.

62
00:04:39,460 --> 00:04:41,030
It'll be tough to find the parts.

63
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:43,240
I've put in my time in the mechanic industry.

64
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:45,400
I asked around and barely managed to get one.

65
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:48,110
It's supposed to get delivered this afternoon.

66
00:04:48,110 --> 00:04:51,070
I'm a pro, aren't I?

67
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:53,800
It wasn't about being a pro.

68
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,280
It was out of her care for you.

69
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:58,510
Sounded like it was quite
an ordeal to get the parts.

70
00:04:58,510 --> 00:05:00,390
She showed up at the crack of dawn today to work.

71
00:05:00,390 --> 00:05:02,720
She always cared for you.

72
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:05,000
Just think of it as paying her back for that.

73
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,940
Stop being mad.

74
00:05:06,940 --> 00:05:08,000
Okay?

75
00:05:12,150 --> 00:05:14,570
[Year 2010]

76
00:05:16,790 --> 00:05:17,990
Here.

77
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:20,030
Take care.

78
00:05:20,030 --> 00:05:21,480
Goodbye.

79
00:05:22,140 --> 00:05:24,740
I hope the memorial service goes well.

80
00:05:24,740 --> 00:05:26,100
Thank you.

81
00:05:30,050 --> 00:05:33,190
His mom died during childbirth.

82
00:05:33,190 --> 00:05:35,830
And his dad ran away, abandoning him.

83
00:05:36,820 --> 00:05:40,170
His grandma was the only one he could depend on.

84
00:05:40,170 --> 00:05:41,580
Gosh, what a pity.

85
00:05:41,580 --> 00:05:43,170
I know.

86
00:05:44,090 --> 00:05:46,450
<i>It's been over a year
since his grandmother passed away</i>

87
00:05:46,450 --> 00:05:48,780
<i>and started living alone.</i>

88
00:05:50,810 --> 00:05:54,810
I brought this from home...

89
00:05:54,810 --> 00:05:57,080
Hey! What took you so long?

90
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:59,030
Hey. What are you doing here?

91
00:05:59,030 --> 00:06:01,440
What do you mean? I'm here to see your grandma.

92
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:02,910
All right...

93
00:06:02,910 --> 00:06:04,240
Whoa.

94
00:06:05,190 --> 00:06:06,760
You brought soju?

95
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:10,310
Hey, she preferred rice wine.

96
00:06:10,310 --> 00:06:11,770
Gosh...

97
00:06:11,770 --> 00:06:15,110
You're only book smart and nothing more.

98
00:06:15,110 --> 00:06:17,800
Aren't you glad I brought this from home?

99
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:21,740
Grandma, Ui Jun brought your favorite rice wine.

100
00:06:21,740 --> 00:06:26,040
Here, have a glass.

101
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,450
What are you doing? Come here.

102
00:06:33,450 --> 00:06:34,850
Okay.

103
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,200
Is this snow?

104
00:06:43,310 --> 00:06:45,070
It's snowing!

105
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:47,420
Wow, daebak.

106
00:06:47,420 --> 00:06:49,010
Wow, so beautiful.

107
00:06:49,010 --> 00:06:52,200
Grandma, do you see this?
Isn't it the first snow of the year?

108
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,360
It is the first snow of the year.

109
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:57,060
<i>Grandma, the snow is so beautiful!</i>

110
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:22,030
Why? What now?

111
00:07:22,030 --> 00:07:23,810
Are you going to cut me off again?

112
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:28,610
Sure, do whatever you want.

113
00:07:29,790 --> 00:07:32,660
But let me set things straight.

114
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:36,000
I did not go to Seoul to drink yesterday.

115
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:40,200
I dealt with something urgent,
and the drinking just happened.

116
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:46,530
I don't know why I'm even
explaining all this to you,

117
00:07:46,530 --> 00:07:49,330
but anyway, despite how much I love drinking,

118
00:07:49,330 --> 00:07:53,790
I don't dump my things on someone else
and go all the way to Seoul to get drunk.

119
00:07:53,790 --> 00:07:56,180
I can't help it if you don't believe me.

120
00:07:59,660 --> 00:08:01,350
I believe you.

121
00:08:02,510 --> 00:08:06,120
- What?
- I trust that you do get your things done.

122
00:08:07,670 --> 00:08:08,820
Okay.

123
00:08:09,550 --> 00:08:10,920
But...

124
00:08:11,870 --> 00:08:14,220
how about taking an alcoholism test?

125
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:16,450
What?

126
00:08:16,450 --> 00:08:18,270
Alcoholism?

127
00:08:19,370 --> 00:08:21,170
Listen to this guy.

128
00:08:21,170 --> 00:08:23,810
I'm fine. Don't treat me like a patient.

129
00:08:23,810 --> 00:08:27,310
Hey, that's for people who can't quit drinking.

130
00:08:27,310 --> 00:08:30,350
I can quit if I really wanted to.

131
00:08:30,350 --> 00:08:34,300
But right now, there's no reason
for me to want to quit.

132
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:36,870
Sure.

133
00:08:36,870 --> 00:08:40,590
If that's what you think,
I can't force you into it.

134
00:08:41,390 --> 00:08:44,920
Hey, let me ask you since we're talking.

135
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:46,850
Why did you quit drinking?

136
00:08:46,850 --> 00:08:49,390
Did you get really sick or something?

137
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:54,440
I was afraid I'd get really sick,
drinking like you do.

138
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:57,940
Or hurt someone else really bad.

139
00:08:57,940 --> 00:08:59,210
Like this.

140
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:05,410
Come early tomorrow.
We have many patients to visit.

141
00:09:15,570 --> 00:09:19,400
[Alcoholism]

142
00:09:21,090 --> 00:09:22,700
[Alcoholism]

143
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:28,150
Me, an alcoholic?

144
00:09:36,020 --> 00:09:37,140
Hey, what's up?

145
00:09:37,140 --> 00:09:39,970
<i>Director Choi had a question for you.</i>

146
00:09:39,970 --> 00:09:43,260
<i>He said you're the only one who can solve this.</i>

147
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,100
Gosh.

148
00:09:47,460 --> 00:09:51,160
He denied my return request
and told me to enjoy my vacation.

149
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:55,020
And now what? I'm the only one who can solve this?

150
00:09:55,020 --> 00:09:56,610
He seeks me out when he needs me.

151
00:09:56,610 --> 00:09:58,890
Hey, tell him to forget it.

152
00:09:58,890 --> 00:09:59,970
<i>Fine.</i>

153
00:09:59,970 --> 00:10:02,070
- Bye.
- Wait.

154
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:05,580
Let me at least hear it.

155
00:10:05,580 --> 00:10:06,960
What did he say to ask me?

156
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:10,030
Is it the electric car motor application analysis

157
00:10:10,030 --> 00:10:11,670
that I worked so hard on?

158
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:14,660
Or the electric car mechanical manual I revamped?

159
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:16,310
Tell him this.

160
00:10:16,310 --> 00:10:19,580
Wait until I've been reinstated.

161
00:10:19,580 --> 00:10:21,040
Right now? No way.

162
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:23,090
I can't tell him anything right now.

163
00:10:23,090 --> 00:10:25,900
Hey, hey. It's nothing like that.

164
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:30,140
<i>The craft beer place you took us to.</i>

165
00:10:30,140 --> 00:10:32,940
<i>He wants to know where that is.
He loved the vibe.</i>

166
00:10:32,940 --> 00:10:34,580
That spot?

167
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,440
That spot...

168
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:41,020
I absolutely can't tell him even more so.

169
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:42,330
Tell him there's no way.

170
00:10:42,330 --> 00:10:44,750
Tell him I said no way I'm telling him.

171
00:10:44,750 --> 00:10:45,840
Got it.

172
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:46,880
Tell him I forgot!

173
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,160
Got it. I'm hanging up.

174
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:49,530
Hey!

175
00:10:52,220 --> 00:10:53,600
How's work?

176
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,060
Is...

177
00:10:55,060 --> 00:10:57,150
everything going well?

178
00:10:57,150 --> 00:10:59,350
How's my replacement doing? Good?

179
00:10:59,350 --> 00:11:01,900
Hey, remember why you're on vacation.

180
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:03,910
Do you want to worry about work?

181
00:11:03,910 --> 00:11:05,500
<i>Your replacement is doing fine.</i>

182
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,550
<i>The company is doing fine.</i>

183
00:11:07,550 --> 00:11:10,320
<i>So, unplug and enjoy your vacation.</i>

184
00:11:14,530 --> 00:11:16,160
All right.

185
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:18,850
Doing just fine without me, huh?

186
00:11:20,610 --> 00:11:22,660
Just wait till I'm back at work.

187
00:11:25,170 --> 00:11:27,030
Of course.

188
00:11:27,030 --> 00:11:30,400
My Geum Ju is a car expert.

189
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:34,380
Hey, she's an invaluable talent to her company.

190
00:11:34,380 --> 00:11:36,470
She was awarded extended leave

191
00:11:36,470 --> 00:11:39,410
for working nonstop for ten years.

192
00:11:40,220 --> 00:11:42,410
Got it. I'll call you back in a bit. Bye.

193
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:44,280
- Geum Ju.
- Yeah?

194
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:46,030
- The butcher...
- Yeah?

195
00:11:46,030 --> 00:11:48,040
wants to get a new delivery van.

196
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,090
He wants to ask you which one you recommend.

197
00:11:50,090 --> 00:11:52,010
- Delivery?
- Yeah.

198
00:11:52,010 --> 00:11:54,790
Gosh, they say talented people
never catch a break.

199
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:58,680
People around us just can't leave you alone!

200
00:12:02,310 --> 00:12:04,270
So tired...

201
00:12:12,580 --> 00:12:15,190
He's quite a character, isn't he?

202
00:12:15,190 --> 00:12:17,640
- What a character.
- Yeah.

203
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:19,820
Bochun's pride.

204
00:12:21,370 --> 00:12:23,170
I want it.

205
00:12:23,170 --> 00:12:24,570
What?

206
00:12:26,700 --> 00:12:28,340
Are you crazy? What did you just say?

207
00:12:28,340 --> 00:12:31,230
You scared me. Why are you yelling?

208
00:12:31,230 --> 00:12:32,710
I know I'm not allowed to drink,

209
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:34,560
but I can't even say I want that?

210
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:35,680
Huh?

211
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:38,350
[Bochun's Treasure!
Bochun's Pride! Hosu Rice Wine!]

212
00:12:38,350 --> 00:12:41,410
I'm so stressed out from not being able to drink.

213
00:12:41,410 --> 00:12:44,420
I didn't know you were talking about that.

214
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,810
What? What were you looking at?

215
00:12:48,530 --> 00:12:50,400
Look at him go.

216
00:12:51,340 --> 00:12:53,210
What? Are you crazy? Insane?

217
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:54,700
What do you think of me?

218
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:56,960
What are you...

219
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:59,090
laughing about?

220
00:12:59,090 --> 00:13:00,600
She's about to explode from

221
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:03,180
the stress because she can't drink.

222
00:13:04,660 --> 00:13:06,160
Hello...

223
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,460
Oh, yes, yes, yes.

224
00:13:08,460 --> 00:13:10,400
I'm on my way to the car center now.

225
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,970
Why don't we go, too?

226
00:13:11,970 --> 00:13:14,100
Noona, you know...

227
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:16,660
would you like to relieve stress
through taekwondo?

228
00:13:16,660 --> 00:13:18,420
Taekwondo?

229
00:13:19,540 --> 00:13:22,590
Gosh, I can barely afford the kids' academies.

230
00:13:22,590 --> 00:13:24,640
I can't.

231
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:27,240
Oh, I see.

232
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:31,110
[Hosu Rice Wine 2+1]

233
00:13:32,530 --> 00:13:35,200
I-I-It's free!

234
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,720
Your loss if you don't take the class.

235
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:37,950
- What?
- Two plus one.

236
00:13:37,950 --> 00:13:40,030
We have a promotion going on.

237
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:41,950
Woo Ri and Na Rah are two.

238
00:13:41,950 --> 00:13:43,630
You'd be one.

239
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,230
[Sociability / Patience / Confidence / Focus]

240
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:20,140
You really don't want to meet her?
[2024 Free Flu Shots]

241
00:14:20,140 --> 00:14:22,120
My granddaughter is a lawyer,

242
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:24,950
and she's a beauty, just like me.

243
00:14:24,950 --> 00:14:27,160
She looks just like you?

244
00:14:28,530 --> 00:14:30,740
Nope. No way.

245
00:14:30,740 --> 00:14:31,900
Why not?

246
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:35,300
That would mean she doesn't listen.

247
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:38,500
I told you to come to the clinic
for your X-rays long ago.

248
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:39,990
You never came.

249
00:14:39,990 --> 00:14:42,600
Fine, I'll come.

250
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,360
You mean it?

251
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:46,670
Keep your promise this time.

252
00:14:46,670 --> 00:14:48,300
Think about it. Really.

253
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:50,190
Okay. Take care.

254
00:14:50,190 --> 00:14:51,970
Goodbye.

255
00:14:51,970 --> 00:14:54,020
Ever since the TA,

256
00:14:54,020 --> 00:14:56,800
her right wrist is not doing well.

257
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:59,860
- Please make an appointment for a wrist series.
- Okay.

258
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:04,580
Doctor, I'd like to make a suggestion.

259
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:08,340
Why don't you stop here?

260
00:15:09,090 --> 00:15:11,950
It's lunch in ten seconds.

261
00:15:11,950 --> 00:15:13,700
Shall we?

262
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:16,840
We'll be back after lunch.

263
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:18,670
<i>Okay.</i>

264
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,240
What a mystery.

265
00:15:37,810 --> 00:15:42,440
Why would such a hotshot Seoul doctor

266
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:45,120
come back here and do that?

267
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:48,820
He couldn't have been pushed
to the cliff's edge like me.

